WEBVTT

00:03.571 --> 00:05.139
Yay! You guys,
the Parent Social's tonight!

00:05.173 --> 00:06.974
Just kidding.
That's terrible news.
Oh, God.

00:07.007 --> 00:08.342
No, no, no, no, no, it's gonna
be fun this year, guys.

00:08.376 --> 00:09.710
I'm your Room Parent.

00:09.743 --> 00:11.212
It's kind of my thing.
Douglas is hosting.

00:11.245 --> 00:13.481
But I really, really need
your help, guys,

00:13.514 --> 00:15.716
'cause I'm gonna be circulating
a petition to get

00:15.749 --> 00:17.351
all of the parents
in our class to agree

00:17.385 --> 00:19.487
not to buy our children phones
until eighth grade.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.655
I call it "Wait Till Eighth."
Oh, Will.

00:21.689 --> 00:23.257
Why?
That's cool.

00:23.291 --> 00:24.425
Guys, seriously.
This is important, okay?

00:24.458 --> 00:26.527
Sophie's already addicted
to my phone.

00:26.560 --> 00:27.928
Next time you see her,
look at her hands.

00:27.961 --> 00:29.263
Her thumbs are frozen
like this.

00:29.297 --> 00:30.531
That's not good.
So I know that it's lame,

00:30.564 --> 00:33.334
but I really need your help
gathering signatures,

00:33.367 --> 00:34.768
and I will be
handing out clipboards.

00:34.802 --> 00:36.437
I'm not holding a clipboard
in my own home.

00:36.470 --> 00:37.838
Yeah.
Clipboard's a no-go.

00:37.871 --> 00:40.208
Sorry, Will. The Parent Social's
like high school.

00:40.241 --> 00:41.275
When the kids
aren't around,

00:41.309 --> 00:42.776
the parent scene becomes
a John Hughes movie.

00:42.810 --> 00:44.178
It's all cliques.

00:44.212 --> 00:45.846
And I don't think I have to
tell you who the losers are.

00:45.879 --> 00:48.516
It's us.
The losers are us.
Yeah, which is fine.

00:48.549 --> 00:50.284
I've never been part
of the cool clique --

00:50.318 --> 00:51.785
or any clique, really.

00:51.819 --> 00:54.288
It was always just me
and the stairwell.

00:54.322 --> 00:57.125
But the point is, you know,
I'm used to it.

00:57.158 --> 00:58.459
Yeah. They think we're weird
because we're single,

00:58.492 --> 00:59.693
but I think
they're jealous.

00:59.727 --> 01:00.894
You know they want to sleep
in the middle

01:00.928 --> 01:02.230
of their beds,

01:02.263 --> 01:04.465
and I spread out
like a starfish.

01:04.498 --> 01:06.134
-Hm.
-Suck it, marrieds!

01:07.335 --> 01:08.802
Be nice to be in love,
though.

01:08.836 --> 01:10.037
Mm.
Yeah, that would be nice.

01:10.070 --> 01:13.774
And, Poppy, you did us
no favors last year.

01:13.807 --> 01:15.209
They called her
Sloppy Poppy.

01:15.243 --> 01:17.278
Ooh!
Hey, I had just finalized
my divorce,

01:17.311 --> 01:18.946
and there was an open bar.
I was fun.

01:18.979 --> 01:21.282
Oh, please. I'm the one who
threw the damn thing last year,

01:21.315 --> 01:22.783
and how was I repaid?

01:22.816 --> 01:24.618
My prize possession
was stolen.

01:24.652 --> 01:26.287
He's talking
about a pen.

01:26.320 --> 01:28.989
It was a Ronald Reagan
White House collectible,

01:29.022 --> 01:33.294
stolen -- by that bastard
right over there, Mark Rush.

01:33.327 --> 01:34.295
The sweet dad
from our class?
Aww.

01:34.328 --> 01:36.330
Now, that is a kind man.

01:36.364 --> 01:37.998
Schmuck.
I even like that guy.

01:38.031 --> 01:39.733
-Hey, guys.
-Hey!

01:39.767 --> 01:41.302
Thank you so much
for your casserole recipe.

01:41.335 --> 01:42.303
Mark: You're so welcome.

01:42.336 --> 01:44.238
Just remember --
375, 40 minutes,

01:44.272 --> 01:46.774
and then peel off the foil
for the final 10.

01:46.807 --> 01:48.442
You're gonna think you died
and went to heaven.
[ Chuckles ]

01:48.476 --> 01:50.144
Hey, Douglas.
Yep.

01:52.012 --> 01:53.147
He's a monster.

01:53.181 --> 01:55.516
Did you forget
that Mark worked for me?

01:55.549 --> 01:58.619
I mentored him. I taught him
everything he knew.

01:58.652 --> 02:00.120
And then he stole
half my patients

02:00.154 --> 02:01.522
and started
his own practice?

02:01.555 --> 02:03.457
And now he's the most popular
guy in the school

02:03.491 --> 02:05.193
and he thinks
he can steal my pen?

02:05.226 --> 02:06.460
How do you know
it was Mark?

02:06.494 --> 02:08.496
You can't just accuse
an innocent man.

02:08.529 --> 02:11.499
Yes, I can, because I'm not
as good a person as you.

02:11.532 --> 02:12.633
You haven't done
a single thing wrong

02:12.666 --> 02:14.668
the whole time
I've known you.

02:14.702 --> 02:16.804
You -- You stop completely
at stop signs.

02:16.837 --> 02:18.339
You give back
extra change.

02:18.372 --> 02:20.474
You're like the Dalai Lama
with longer hair.

02:20.508 --> 02:22.310
Thanks.

02:22.343 --> 02:24.212
All right, I know
what it's gonna take

02:24.245 --> 02:26.046
to get your help
with the petition.

02:26.079 --> 02:27.147
Babysitting. Hit me.

02:27.181 --> 02:28.782
Bingo.
I need Saturday night.

02:28.816 --> 02:30.184
-I want Tuesday.
-June.

02:30.218 --> 02:31.285
The month of June.

02:31.319 --> 02:32.986
You know what, actually?
Let's make a deal.

02:33.020 --> 02:34.822
Saturday nights
into Sunday mornings

02:34.855 --> 02:36.990
Yes!
and a Thursday sneak attack
whenever we feel like it.

02:37.024 --> 02:37.858
She's good.

02:37.891 --> 02:38.859
All right.

02:38.892 --> 02:40.461
-Yes!
-Yes!

02:40.494 --> 02:43.030
Oh, God, I love exploiting
a person in need.

02:43.063 --> 02:46.166
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:48.402 --> 02:50.504
[ Dance music plays ]

02:50.538 --> 02:53.040
[ Indistinct conversations,
laughter ]

02:53.073 --> 02:54.842
Okay, visual aids are in place,
and my special

02:54.875 --> 02:55.843
guest speaker is on the way.

02:55.876 --> 02:56.810
Trust me.

02:56.844 --> 02:57.845
The person I am bringing

02:57.878 --> 03:00.147
is going to blow your minds.

03:00.180 --> 03:01.682
It's Dewan.
Obviously Dewan.
The pediatrician
you're sleeping with.

03:01.715 --> 03:03.016
Yes, okay.

03:03.050 --> 03:04.318
-[ Sighs ]
-Douglas, I can't believe

03:04.352 --> 03:06.053
you agreed to host
this wack-ass party again.

03:06.086 --> 03:07.988
Oh, I have my reasons.

03:08.021 --> 03:10.491
Big plans are afoot
this evening.

03:10.524 --> 03:11.759
[ Laughs ]

03:11.792 --> 03:14.362
Well, that's not shady.

03:14.395 --> 03:15.763
All right, until 8:00,

03:15.796 --> 03:16.864
you will mingle
with parents in your zone.

03:16.897 --> 03:18.098
There's a map on the back

03:18.131 --> 03:19.166
as well as talking points.

03:19.199 --> 03:20.834
Angie, your card's already
on the ground!

03:20.868 --> 03:22.770
I have a weak grip.

03:22.803 --> 03:24.104
Is anybody interested in wearing

03:24.137 --> 03:25.773
a cellphone costume later?

03:25.806 --> 03:27.275
Super breathable,
commercial quality rental...

03:27.308 --> 03:28.942
We all know who's wearing
the costume, Will.

03:28.976 --> 03:30.444
Yeah, and it is my size.
I'm pretty psyched about it.

03:30.478 --> 03:32.446
Okay, gang. Let's fan out.

03:32.480 --> 03:33.714
Oh, no.

03:33.747 --> 03:34.715
Put me in a different zone.

03:34.748 --> 03:36.116
I have the worst clique.

03:36.149 --> 03:37.518
We don't have cliques.
This is Hilltop.

03:37.551 --> 03:39.453
Oh, you sweet, dumb man.

03:39.487 --> 03:40.688
Look around.

03:40.721 --> 03:44.057
You got the hippies...

03:44.091 --> 03:46.126
the jocks...

03:46.159 --> 03:47.695
the power couples...

03:47.728 --> 03:49.029
the wannabe swingers --

03:49.062 --> 03:50.464
don't go to their house
for a nightcap.

03:50.498 --> 03:51.532
But the scariest

03:51.565 --> 03:52.933
are the class trendsetters --

03:52.966 --> 03:55.703
Jackie, Molly, and Lex.

03:55.736 --> 03:57.271
[ Sighs ] I call them...

03:57.305 --> 03:59.039
the We'vers.

03:59.072 --> 04:01.709
[ School bell rings ]

04:01.742 --> 04:03.877
We've noticed you haven't picked
a dish for the bake sale yet.

04:03.911 --> 04:06.213
We've sent you the SignUpGenius
three times.

04:06.246 --> 04:07.715
We've been
very disappointed.

04:07.748 --> 04:11.452
**

04:11.485 --> 04:13.287
Jackie thinks she's so cool
because her husband

04:13.321 --> 04:14.322
writes for "Gotham."

04:14.355 --> 04:15.956
All five seasons?
[ Sighs ]

04:15.989 --> 04:17.325
Please, don't make me
talk to them.

04:17.358 --> 04:20.894
Angie, that's what the note card
is for, okay?

04:20.928 --> 04:23.464
I think you will find I have
a pretty great ear for dialogue.

04:23.497 --> 04:27.134
There are a shocking number
of stage directions,

04:27.167 --> 04:29.670
but I'll try.

04:29.703 --> 04:32.473
"...which puts kids at risk
for a permanent hump

04:32.506 --> 04:34.808
on the back
of their necks.

04:34.842 --> 04:36.644
It's called tech neck."

04:36.677 --> 04:37.778
I got the jocks.

04:37.811 --> 04:39.513
Ugh. Lucky.

04:41.482 --> 04:42.816
Where'd they go?!

04:42.850 --> 04:44.618
**

04:44.652 --> 04:46.286
There she is!

04:46.320 --> 04:48.121
Oh. [ Chuckles ]
My guest speaker!

04:48.155 --> 04:49.790
Okay, now, my speech
isn't till 8:00,

04:49.823 --> 04:51.291
so that gives us
an hour and a half

04:51.325 --> 04:52.460
to mingle
with the parents.

04:52.493 --> 04:53.827
Parents? [ Chuckles ]

04:53.861 --> 04:55.463
You said
this was a high-profile event.

04:55.496 --> 04:58.532
Uh, it is.
Every single parent is here.

04:58.566 --> 05:00.033
Even Jessica's mom.
She never comes to these things.

05:00.067 --> 05:01.669
Yeah, no,
I can't go in there.

05:01.702 --> 05:03.837
They will eat me alive.
Those parents worship me.

05:03.871 --> 05:05.973
It's always, "Dr. Dewan,
can you cure my kid?"

05:06.006 --> 05:07.140
"Dr. Dewan,
you're so hot."

05:07.174 --> 05:08.642
It's a real hassle.

05:08.676 --> 05:10.310
Monica?

05:10.344 --> 05:11.645
Mm-hmm?
These are
just normal people

05:11.679 --> 05:13.847
trying to enjoy
an evening without kids.

05:13.881 --> 05:15.649
[ Exhales sharply ]
Okay.

05:15.683 --> 05:17.718
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]
Okay.

05:19.152 --> 05:20.654
It's happening.
They saw me.

05:20.688 --> 05:22.122
This is not good.

05:22.155 --> 05:23.223
None of them
are blinking.

05:25.359 --> 05:27.294
They're gonna start to move
towards me at some point.

05:27.327 --> 05:28.829
One of the moms
just licked her lips.

05:28.862 --> 05:30.197
All right,
the traps are set.

05:30.230 --> 05:31.699
All I got to do
is sit back

05:31.732 --> 05:33.701
and wait for the rat
to smell the cheese.

05:33.734 --> 05:35.803
Mark's the rat.

05:35.836 --> 05:37.304
Traps?
Really, Douglas?

05:37.337 --> 05:40.474
My TV's connected
to all the security cameras.

05:40.508 --> 05:42.643
Every room in the house
is being watched

05:42.676 --> 05:44.177
like the "M.A.S.H." finale,

05:44.211 --> 05:46.514
especially my study,
where I've laid out

05:46.547 --> 05:49.817
all of my most valuable,
most portable possessions.

05:49.850 --> 05:53.687
And when that Judas steals,
everyone's gonna be watching.

05:53.721 --> 05:56.990
As an extra precaution,
I got a guy on the ground.

05:57.024 --> 05:58.526
It's me.
I'm on the ground.

05:58.559 --> 06:00.828
Relax.
Chill mode. Okay.

06:00.861 --> 06:02.329
I'm a "bartender,"

06:02.362 --> 06:05.098
but I'm really just here
to keep an eye on Mark.

06:05.132 --> 06:07.334
Once someone tells me
who he is.

06:07.367 --> 06:09.202
Okay, I think this is
a terrible plan,

06:09.236 --> 06:11.371
and I once took all the kids
to the beach.

06:11.405 --> 06:13.006
Let's say
he did steal the pen.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.775
So what?
He deserves a second chance.

06:14.808 --> 06:16.710
Save it for Earth Day.

06:16.744 --> 06:20.213
He's not a person.
He's a backstabbing turd.

06:20.247 --> 06:22.115
He must be
taken off the streets.

06:22.149 --> 06:26.119
This is like "Spy Games,"
you know? Yeah.

06:26.153 --> 06:28.055
Okay, Miggy.
I hate to break it to you.

06:28.088 --> 06:29.523
Huh?
You're not
gonna catch Mark.

06:29.557 --> 06:30.558
You don't know that.

06:30.591 --> 06:32.460
[ Quietly ]
Yes, I do!

06:32.493 --> 06:35.162
I stole the pen,
Miggy.

06:36.430 --> 06:38.899
Ooh, Miggy conflicted.

06:38.932 --> 06:46.874
**

06:46.907 --> 06:47.975
Hey.

06:49.309 --> 06:51.945
Uh, "Did you know
smartphone dependence

06:51.979 --> 06:53.547
produces the same
brain response

06:53.581 --> 06:55.783
as a hard-core
gambling addiction?

06:55.816 --> 06:57.451
Don't love those odds."

06:57.485 --> 06:59.553
Are you literally reading off
an index card right now?

06:59.587 --> 07:02.122
Yeah, it's a whole thing.
Will gave me a script.

07:02.155 --> 07:03.290
Ugh.
He scripts everything.

07:03.323 --> 07:05.125
Who does he think he is,
Aaron Sorkin?

07:05.158 --> 07:07.495
Sorry. My husband writes
for "Gotham."

07:07.528 --> 07:10.464
[ Inhales sharply ]
Will is obsessed with control.

07:10.498 --> 07:11.499
[ Chuckles ]

07:11.532 --> 07:13.133
Let me guess.
He brought a puppet.

07:13.166 --> 07:14.468
Or a tiny
smoke machine.

07:14.502 --> 07:17.070
Will is a smoke machine.
Am I right?

07:17.104 --> 07:17.871
[ Chuckles ]

07:19.507 --> 07:20.741
Well, at least
you have better taste

07:20.774 --> 07:22.409
in clothes
than you do in friends.

07:22.442 --> 07:25.613
I am loving
that tuxedo ensemble.

07:25.646 --> 07:26.780
Oh. Really?

07:26.814 --> 07:28.682
Mm-hmm. Totally.
Mm-hmm.
Yeah.

07:28.716 --> 07:32.352
I don't care
what my therapist says.

07:32.385 --> 07:35.823
You do know that Will brought
a cellphone costume

07:35.856 --> 07:36.790
to wear tonight, right?

07:36.824 --> 07:38.125
[ Laughter ]
Wait, no!

07:38.158 --> 07:40.794
Hot.
I'm dying.

07:40.828 --> 07:42.029
Oh, my God.
Tell us more.

07:42.062 --> 07:45.866
Oh, he has a Hilltop Elementary
bomber jacket.

07:45.899 --> 07:48.468
The school doesn't sell those.
That means he made it.

07:48.502 --> 07:50.804
[ Laughter ]

07:50.838 --> 07:52.806
Wait. Angie.

07:52.840 --> 07:54.041
[ Gasps ]

07:54.074 --> 07:56.409
Are you hilarious?

07:57.678 --> 07:58.879
I think I am.

07:58.912 --> 08:01.649
[ Laughter ]

08:01.682 --> 08:03.684
We've never really
talked to you before.

08:03.717 --> 08:05.819
You actually have,
like a hundred times,

08:05.853 --> 08:06.854
but it's okay.

08:06.887 --> 08:08.455
[ Laughter ]

08:08.488 --> 08:09.623
Whoo!

08:09.657 --> 08:11.024
**

08:14.995 --> 08:16.296
7:15 huddle, right on time.

08:16.329 --> 08:17.798
Okay, so, where are we
with signatures?

08:17.831 --> 08:19.299
My gut tells me 10?

08:19.332 --> 08:20.167
Zero.
Nothing.

08:20.200 --> 08:21.368
What signatures?

08:21.401 --> 08:23.136
Really?
No new signatures?

08:23.170 --> 08:23.971
Well, I'm doing great
in my zone.

08:24.004 --> 08:25.673
I'm in
with the We'vers.

08:25.706 --> 08:27.507
Poppy: What? Really?

08:27.541 --> 08:29.710
That's surprising.
You hate those mean ladies.

08:29.743 --> 08:32.646
Well, that was until I realized
that they get me.

08:32.680 --> 08:33.814
They think I'm funny.

08:33.847 --> 08:35.182
You're not funny.

08:35.215 --> 08:36.817
I am
when I'm dunking on Will.

08:36.850 --> 08:38.552
[ Chuckles ]
Stings a little,

08:38.586 --> 08:40.353
but hey, if it gets them
to sign on the line.

08:40.387 --> 08:41.354
Could you get them
to wear the button?

08:41.388 --> 08:43.156
No. No chance.
[ Rattling ]

08:43.190 --> 08:45.492
But we've been talking,
and we've noticed

08:45.525 --> 08:47.695
that your girlfriend's
hitting the sauce pretty hard.

08:47.728 --> 08:48.929
Did you just "we've" him?

08:48.962 --> 08:50.764
Yeah. I did.

08:50.798 --> 08:52.933
Yes, my lady is on
a bullet train to Wobble Town,

08:52.966 --> 08:54.201
but for good reason.

08:54.234 --> 08:55.502
Anne, your kid
doesn't have ADHD.

08:55.535 --> 08:57.204
That's the sugar
you pour down her throat.

08:57.237 --> 08:59.006
There. I said it.
Sugar's a drug. Next!

08:59.039 --> 09:00.507
You did this.
Keep 'em coming.

09:00.540 --> 09:01.942
Zach: My kid still wets
the bed.

09:01.975 --> 09:05.045
Zach, your son is 25 years old.
Take them to a urologist.

09:05.078 --> 09:07.014
[ Echoing ] Next!
Have I tried cutting her off?
Yes.

09:07.047 --> 09:08.682
Not gonna do that again.

09:08.716 --> 09:10.550
Where the hell is
that Mark?

09:10.584 --> 09:13.286
Probably too ashamed
to show his face.

09:13.320 --> 09:15.555
Hey,
how are y'all doing?

09:15.589 --> 09:18.692
There's the rat.
How dare you show your face?

09:18.726 --> 09:20.193
Hey, Mark's so nice.

09:20.227 --> 09:21.895
Look, he brought
a full pound cake.

09:21.929 --> 09:24.698
And look, he loves
his age-appropriate wife.

09:24.732 --> 09:25.966
Let it go?

09:25.999 --> 09:28.068
Did Reagan
let Gorbachev go?

09:28.101 --> 09:30.771
I will not back down!

09:30.804 --> 09:32.973
Miggy, you've got to
hold it together.

09:33.006 --> 09:34.608
I'm freaking out,
you know?

09:34.642 --> 09:36.043
I'm supposed to be
Douglas' eyeballs.

09:36.076 --> 09:37.544
Eyeballs
don't have secrets.

09:37.577 --> 09:39.780
Eyeballs are supposed to be
loyal to the brain.

09:39.813 --> 09:40.781
Be loyal to me.

09:40.814 --> 09:42.650
I'm your boss
and your landlord.

09:42.683 --> 09:43.984
And, unless
you were lying last week,

09:44.017 --> 09:46.119
your favorite person
to nap next to.

09:46.153 --> 09:47.554
It wouldn't rock my world
to find out

09:47.587 --> 09:49.790
Angie was a liar and a thief,
but you're my idol.

09:49.823 --> 09:52.960
There's still one question
that haunts me.

09:52.993 --> 09:54.461
Why?

09:54.494 --> 09:55.629
Haunts you?

09:55.663 --> 09:57.831
You just found out
10 minutes ago.

09:57.865 --> 10:01.034
And I didn't steal the pen.
Sloppy Poppy did.

10:02.670 --> 10:04.672
[ Slurring ]
Now that I'm divorced,
my life's my own again.

10:04.705 --> 10:06.907
I am taking
a pizza-making class,

10:06.940 --> 10:08.976
I am become very vocal
on Yelp,

10:09.009 --> 10:10.744
and I --

10:10.778 --> 10:11.945
What are you having?

10:11.979 --> 10:14.147
Uh...

10:15.649 --> 10:17.785
...them digits.

10:17.818 --> 10:19.286
Poppy: And the rest is
all a blur.

10:19.319 --> 10:21.288
Somehow I woke up at a bus stop
in Torrance.

10:21.321 --> 10:22.622
How I got there,
I'll never know.

10:22.656 --> 10:23.623
I assume it was by bus.

10:23.657 --> 10:25.125
Anyway,
I kept thinking

10:25.158 --> 10:26.293
that Douglas
would forget about it,

10:26.326 --> 10:27.627
but now he's obsessed
with taking Mark down,

10:27.661 --> 10:28.962
and Mark's the best!

10:28.996 --> 10:30.530
So where's the pen?

10:30.563 --> 10:33.133
Where is any pen, Miggy?
I don't know. It's a pen.

10:33.166 --> 10:34.467
You got to tell Douglas
the truth.

10:34.501 --> 10:36.003
I know. I should.

10:36.036 --> 10:37.971
But Douglas thinks of me
as a saint,

10:38.005 --> 10:39.873
and honestly,
I love that,

10:39.907 --> 10:41.174
because it means
I get to yell at him

10:41.208 --> 10:42.542
about all the things
he does wrong,

10:42.575 --> 10:44.177
and yelling at Douglas is
one of my favorite things to do.

10:44.211 --> 10:46.680
Now, if he finds out
I stole his pen

10:46.714 --> 10:48.481
and lied about it
for a year,

10:48.515 --> 10:50.550
he never has to
listen to me again.

10:50.583 --> 10:52.853
I was just about to change
his mind about Tucker Carlson.

10:52.886 --> 10:54.287
But what about Mark?

10:54.321 --> 10:55.989
You're really gonna let him
take the fall?

10:56.023 --> 10:59.459
What about Tucker Carlson?
Uh --

10:59.492 --> 11:01.661
A tour is not necessary,
Douglas. I've seen your house.

11:01.695 --> 11:04.698
Well, you can see it again,
give us a chance to catch up.

11:04.732 --> 11:05.699
So, how you been?

11:05.733 --> 11:07.300
Not great.

11:07.334 --> 11:09.302
My dad's not responding
to the radiation and --

11:09.336 --> 11:11.171
Yeah, that's rough.
Let's walk, huh?

11:12.339 --> 11:13.473
Jackie: Oh, my God.

11:13.506 --> 11:15.142
Remember the Vegetable
of the Day e-mail

11:15.175 --> 11:16.143
that Will sent
about lunches?

11:16.176 --> 11:18.145
Oh, my God!
The worst.

11:18.178 --> 11:20.480
He cares so much.

11:20.513 --> 11:21.982
Molly: Some of us care
just as much,

11:22.015 --> 11:24.718
and we waited our turn
for nothing.

11:24.752 --> 11:26.720
Aw. I was supposed
to hand down Room Parent

11:26.754 --> 11:28.021
to Molly this year.

11:28.055 --> 11:30.057
Being Room Parent
was all I had.

11:30.090 --> 11:31.691
I do not want to go back
to life coaching.

11:31.725 --> 11:34.895
Will weaseled his way in
with a million stupid ideas.

11:34.928 --> 11:36.696
Remember
Teacher Sleepovers?

11:36.730 --> 11:38.698
Oh.
Pimp My Calculator?

11:38.732 --> 11:40.033
-Ugh.
-Or tonight.

11:40.067 --> 11:41.869
These socials are meant
for us to blow off steam,

11:41.902 --> 11:43.203
but instead,
every two minutes,

11:43.236 --> 11:45.605
he comes up with a petition
saying, "Hey, gang."

11:45.638 --> 11:47.674
Hey, gang.
How's it going?

11:47.707 --> 11:49.676
Just wondering if you got
a chance to put your Jen Hancock

11:49.709 --> 11:50.844
on the petition
for Wait For Eighth.

11:50.878 --> 11:51.678
Hey, Will.

11:51.711 --> 11:53.046
Hi, Lexi.

11:53.080 --> 11:54.481
[ Sighing ]
Oh, my God.

11:55.648 --> 11:58.518
Uh, you know, Will, right now
really isn't a good time.

11:58.551 --> 12:00.620
Oh, okay.
I'm so sorry.

12:00.653 --> 12:02.522
I'm off to the ol' sauna
to don the cellphone costume.

12:02.555 --> 12:04.892
Sure you don't want to wear it?
Last chance.

12:04.925 --> 12:05.893
No?

12:05.926 --> 12:07.460
Okay. Bye.

12:07.494 --> 12:09.696
Hey, guys!

12:09.729 --> 12:11.799
[ Laughter ]

12:11.832 --> 12:13.633
You're so bad,
Angie!

12:13.666 --> 12:15.035
I hate him so much.

12:15.068 --> 12:17.037
Yeah. He's --
Uh, yeah.

12:17.070 --> 12:19.940
It's so great you're on our side
about Will.

12:19.973 --> 12:21.942
Now you can help us.
Help you what?

12:21.975 --> 12:25.378
Take him down.
So Molly can become Room Parent.

12:25.412 --> 12:27.714
**

12:27.747 --> 12:29.482
Mm.

12:29.516 --> 12:34.121
**

12:34.154 --> 12:36.289
Alexa,
turn on the trophy lights.

12:36.323 --> 12:37.090
Alexa: Okay.

12:39.159 --> 12:40.727
Wow.
These all yours?

12:40.760 --> 12:41.995
Yes.

12:42.029 --> 12:44.164
Go ahead.
Pick 'em up.

12:44.197 --> 12:45.398
Uh, no.
I-I don't need to --

12:45.432 --> 12:47.134
Pick them up, Mark.

12:47.167 --> 12:52.239
**

12:52.272 --> 12:54.641
Ah. That was signed
by Pete Rose,

12:54.674 --> 12:56.309
Mr. Charlie Hustle
himself.

12:56.343 --> 12:59.479
I met him at
a wet T-shirt contest in Reno.

12:59.512 --> 13:00.513
There's a class act.

13:00.547 --> 13:03.984
**

13:04.017 --> 13:06.353
"Thanks for making gorgeous
so easy.

13:06.386 --> 13:08.288
Best wishes, Bo Derek."

13:08.321 --> 13:12.459
Her Botox work alone
paid for my big car.

13:12.492 --> 13:15.495
Yep, that's just one of the many
treasures that I've amassed.

13:15.528 --> 13:19.166
Anyway, I should probably
get back to my guests now.

13:20.700 --> 13:21.801
No, no, no, no.

13:21.835 --> 13:24.804
You stay
and admire my collection.

13:24.838 --> 13:26.706
Oh, I should really
get back to my wife --

13:26.739 --> 13:29.642
You'll stay
and admire my collection.

13:29.676 --> 13:30.710
Okay.

13:32.913 --> 13:36.549
[ Quietly ] Alexa, set
the temperature to 90 degrees.

13:36.583 --> 13:38.051
Alexa: The heat is set to 90.
[ Door closes ]

13:41.588 --> 13:42.555
The sauna's occupied!

13:42.589 --> 13:43.790
Oh.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.158
[ Slurring ]
Hey, I'm leaving, okay?

13:45.192 --> 13:47.360
Some mom had her kid call me
so I could hear his cough.

13:47.394 --> 13:48.528
It was just the worst.

13:48.561 --> 13:49.529
Are you dressed
like a phone?

13:49.562 --> 13:50.630
I am.

13:50.663 --> 13:51.631
And you can't leave.

13:51.664 --> 13:52.832
I need you
for the presentation.

13:54.567 --> 13:56.669
**

13:56.703 --> 13:57.704
What's in it for me?

13:59.172 --> 14:00.974
Oh, you mean sexy time.
Mm-hmm.

14:01.008 --> 14:02.042
Boop, boop, boop...

14:02.075 --> 14:02.809
Oh!

14:02.842 --> 14:04.144
...boop.

14:04.177 --> 14:06.646
If I let you dial me,
you'll stay?

14:06.679 --> 14:08.148
Mm-hmm.

14:08.181 --> 14:11.184
Operator,
I got disconnected.

14:11.218 --> 14:13.053
Can you connect me?

14:15.088 --> 14:16.356
Ooh.

14:16.389 --> 14:18.691
Yes, ma'am.
We can help you with that.

14:18.725 --> 14:20.493
You could either
consult your directory

14:20.527 --> 14:22.329
or for ten cents --
Mm-hmm.

14:22.362 --> 14:24.831
Okay. Mark is in the study
right now.

14:24.864 --> 14:26.099
Turn on that camera.

14:26.133 --> 14:31.939
**

14:31.972 --> 14:33.606
He's got Bo.
He's got Bo!

14:33.640 --> 14:35.375
Okay, everybody,
gather around.

14:35.408 --> 14:36.709
Zoom in, Miggy.
Zoom!

14:36.743 --> 14:39.346
Douglas, I'm not the eyeballs
you thought I was.

14:39.379 --> 14:40.948
Oh, crap on a cracker.

14:40.981 --> 14:42.950
Someone's having sex
in my sauna!

14:42.983 --> 14:45.218
Yeah, I know it's roaming,
but I still want data!

14:45.252 --> 14:46.219
Sorry.

14:46.253 --> 14:47.720
Oh, that's great.
Sorry.

14:47.754 --> 14:49.456
I think
that's Will.

14:49.489 --> 14:52.525
By the amount of apologizing
happening, it definitely is.

14:52.559 --> 14:54.127
4 and the 6.
Touch the 4 and the 6.

14:54.161 --> 14:56.196
Is that cellphone role-play?
Oh, my...

14:56.229 --> 14:57.497
I'm going in the canyon.
Can you hear me?

15:01.668 --> 15:03.036
[ Imitates ringing ]
Incoming call.

15:03.070 --> 15:05.472
[ Imitates buzzing ]
Did someone just get a text?

15:05.505 --> 15:06.806
Will, Will,
before you go out there,

15:06.839 --> 15:09.109
I have to tell you
something.
[ Imitates beep ]

15:09.142 --> 15:11.444
Gonna have to put that on hold,
Angie. It's 8:00.
No, I really have
to tell you something.

15:11.478 --> 15:12.679
Will you come back --
No -- Okay.
Speech time, baby.

15:13.813 --> 15:15.215
God, what do we do?

15:15.248 --> 15:17.050
[ Amplified ]
Check one, check one.

15:17.084 --> 15:18.385
Can I get a level up on this?

15:18.418 --> 15:19.719
Nope? Okay.

15:19.752 --> 15:21.788
Uh, welcome, everyone.

15:21.821 --> 15:22.655
Are we having fun?

15:22.689 --> 15:23.957
Not as much as you.

15:23.991 --> 15:26.559
[ Laughter ]

15:26.593 --> 15:28.828
That's true. I am having
a very good time.

15:28.861 --> 15:30.230
[ Breathes deeply ]

15:30.263 --> 15:32.132
But now it's time
to get a little serious.
Angie. Psst.

15:32.165 --> 15:33.633
A phone makes
our lives easier.

15:33.666 --> 15:35.302
Oh, right.
I'm still popular.

15:35.335 --> 15:37.470
But it also makes
our lives less present.

15:37.504 --> 15:39.672
Isn't this hilarious?
He has no idea.

15:39.706 --> 15:42.475
[ Laughter ]

15:42.509 --> 15:43.676
Now, you guys have
seen enough of me.

15:43.710 --> 15:45.245
Yeah, we have.

15:45.278 --> 15:47.414
[ Laughter ]

15:47.447 --> 15:48.481
Ha!

15:48.515 --> 15:50.850
[ Laughter continues ]

15:50.883 --> 15:52.185
I missed that, but let's save
all our questions

15:52.219 --> 15:54.021
till the end of the speeches,
please.

15:54.054 --> 15:55.655
Will. Hey. Psst.
It is my privilege...

15:55.688 --> 15:57.790
...to bring here
our very special guest...
Wait.

15:57.824 --> 16:00.693
taker of tonsils,
fixer of boo-boos.

16:00.727 --> 16:04.864
Please put your hands together
for Dr. Monica Dewan.

16:04.897 --> 16:08.301
[ Applause ]

16:08.335 --> 16:11.038
Angie. Check it.
Dewan: So, does your child
have a cellphone?

16:11.071 --> 16:12.872
Molly: This is our ticket
to take back the room.

16:12.905 --> 16:15.842
But...
[ Scoffs ]

16:15.875 --> 16:18.645
...being the Room Parent is
really important to Will.

16:18.678 --> 16:20.313
I mean, he got
business cards made.

16:20.347 --> 16:21.714
We told him
never to pass them out,

16:21.748 --> 16:23.483
but still,
he's got 'em.

16:23.516 --> 16:25.018
After I e-mail the sex tape
to the principal,

16:25.052 --> 16:27.154
that dork is out of here.

16:27.187 --> 16:30.057
Assuming the principal's not,
like, super into it.

16:30.090 --> 16:31.824
He's worse
than Sloppy Poppy.

16:31.858 --> 16:33.360
[ Laughter ]

16:33.393 --> 16:35.462
...a personal parenting choice
around cellphones.

16:35.495 --> 16:36.529
As a doctor, um,

16:36.563 --> 16:39.366
it's not really
my field of expertise.

16:39.399 --> 16:40.833
Hey.

16:40.867 --> 16:42.135
Can I see your phone?

16:42.169 --> 16:43.303
I want to re-watch
that part of the video

16:43.336 --> 16:44.971
where Dewan
pulls out his antenna.

16:45.004 --> 16:46.973
[ Laughter ]
So good.

16:47.006 --> 16:48.508
And deleted.
[ Gasps ]

16:48.541 --> 16:50.310
What?!
I was gonna watch that video
multiple times.

16:50.343 --> 16:51.311
You know what?

16:51.344 --> 16:53.313
Will might be a dork,
all right,

16:53.346 --> 16:55.815
but dorks are just people
who care a lot,

16:55.848 --> 16:58.818
and Will cares
more than any of us.

16:58.851 --> 17:00.853
I mean, h-h-he shows up
on Saturdays at school

17:00.887 --> 17:02.322
to pick up trash
in the schoolyard.

17:02.355 --> 17:04.724
He buys art supplies
with his own money.

17:04.757 --> 17:07.160
And he rented
that dumb cellphone costume,

17:07.194 --> 17:09.996
which he is never going to
get his deposit back on,

17:10.029 --> 17:12.399
because our children
matter to him.

17:12.432 --> 17:14.767
Dewan: ...in closing,
please respect my office hours.

17:14.801 --> 17:16.103
They're there
for a reason.

17:16.136 --> 17:17.504
Angie, hot water and lemon
would be wonderful. Thank you.

17:17.537 --> 17:19.839
We all saw you and Dewan
in the sauna.

17:19.872 --> 17:20.773
Douglas has cameras
everywhere.

17:20.807 --> 17:22.109
What?!

17:22.142 --> 17:24.777
Um, when you say "saw us,"
do you mean...

17:24.811 --> 17:25.945
Yes. Yes.

17:25.978 --> 17:27.280
This is so humiliating.

17:27.314 --> 17:29.282
Nobody touch me.
Just clear a path.

17:29.316 --> 17:31.184
Wait, Monica.
We need signatures.

17:31.218 --> 17:32.519
I'm going home.

17:32.552 --> 17:34.687
I'll meet you later
if you bring that phone costume.

17:34.721 --> 17:36.156
[ Door closes ]

17:38.325 --> 17:40.960
Screens are known
to impair sleep,

17:40.993 --> 17:42.795
and sleep disturbances can cause
other health problems,

17:42.829 --> 17:44.831
like stunted growth.

17:46.166 --> 17:51.238
And...that should be
keeping you up at night.

17:51.271 --> 17:53.140
I'm Angie D'Amato,

17:53.173 --> 17:55.142
and I'm going to
wait till eighth!

17:55.175 --> 17:57.777
**

17:57.810 --> 17:59.112
You memorized
your index card.

17:59.146 --> 18:01.114
Yeah, well...

18:01.148 --> 18:02.815
it was a really long line
to the bathroom.

18:02.849 --> 18:04.884
Angie.
Are you the worst?

18:04.917 --> 18:07.620
Yeah! Yeah!
I think I am!

18:07.654 --> 18:10.157
And you know what?
Maybe we all are.

18:10.190 --> 18:11.324
Maybe we're the losers,

18:11.358 --> 18:13.826
but I'd rather be one of us
than one of you!

18:13.860 --> 18:15.628
[ Gasping ]

18:15.662 --> 18:16.829
Except for you, Mark.
You're the best.

18:16.863 --> 18:18.298
Will:
Glad you're here, Mark.

18:18.331 --> 18:19.632
You're just such a nice guy.
Such a nice guy.

18:19.666 --> 18:21.067
He's the best.
Love Mark.
Love Mark.

18:21.100 --> 18:22.169
You're the man, Mark.

18:22.202 --> 18:23.970
It's true.
Mark's a great man.

18:24.003 --> 18:25.238
He's the homey
right there.

18:25.272 --> 18:29.409
I am so sick of everyone
siding with Mark.

18:29.442 --> 18:30.510
He's a thief.

18:30.543 --> 18:31.578
[ Gasping ]

18:31.611 --> 18:33.180
All right.
No, Douglas, he isn't.

18:33.213 --> 18:34.681
Mark didn't steal
your pen.

18:34.714 --> 18:35.915
Yes, I did.

18:35.948 --> 18:37.517
[ Gasping ]
Ha!

18:37.550 --> 18:39.018
How?
I thought I stole it.

18:39.051 --> 18:39.819
What?

18:39.852 --> 18:42.622
You did, and then...

18:42.655 --> 18:43.523
[ Slurps ]

18:43.556 --> 18:44.291
Mmm.

18:44.324 --> 18:46.493
Wow.

18:46.526 --> 18:47.960
Nice hands.

18:47.994 --> 18:49.796
My grandma used to call
brothers like you

18:49.829 --> 18:52.465
"easy on the eyes."

18:52.499 --> 18:54.867
I knew it!
Vindication.

18:54.901 --> 18:56.303
I was just trying
to even the score.

18:56.336 --> 18:59.339
You worked me so hard --
nights, weekends.

18:59.372 --> 19:01.308
No matter how many
atypical moles I found,

19:01.341 --> 19:02.375
it was never enough.

19:02.409 --> 19:03.643
And that gives you
the right

19:03.676 --> 19:05.312
to steal another man's
Reagan pen?

19:05.345 --> 19:06.346
It filled the void!

19:06.379 --> 19:07.480
And yes, I admit,

19:07.514 --> 19:10.317
it made me feel important
because...

19:10.350 --> 19:11.818
it made me feel like you.

19:11.851 --> 19:12.985
-Aww.
-Is that so bad?

19:13.019 --> 19:14.153
[ Crowd "Aww"ing ]

19:14.187 --> 19:15.322
No. No, it's not bad
at all.

19:15.355 --> 19:16.389
Thank you for telling
the truth, Mark.

19:16.423 --> 19:18.325
That's real, bro.

19:18.358 --> 19:19.692
I'm human.

19:22.161 --> 19:23.963
Who cares about Mark
and the stupid pen?!

19:23.996 --> 19:25.532
The real thief here
is Will.

19:25.565 --> 19:28.134
What?
Molly was next in line
for Room Parent.

19:28.167 --> 19:31.137
Well, it looks like you waited
in the wrong line, bitch!

19:31.170 --> 19:32.805
[ Gasping ]

19:32.839 --> 19:34.307
D'Amato mic drop!

19:34.341 --> 19:35.041
Oh, that's a rental.
Oh!
[ Feedback ]

19:38.911 --> 19:40.313
Welcome home, Mr. President.

19:40.347 --> 19:42.649
I'll love you
like Nancy never could.

19:42.682 --> 19:44.050
Hm.
That's a good pen.

19:44.083 --> 19:45.818
I could see wanting
to steal that thing.

19:45.852 --> 19:48.688
All right, I know I've given up
the moral high ground.

19:48.721 --> 19:50.557
I'm never gonna live that down,
am I, Douglas?

19:50.590 --> 19:52.325
Correct.
But if I'm gonna be honest,

19:52.359 --> 19:54.160
I kind of respect you more.

19:54.193 --> 19:57.564
I mean, you lied to me
for a year. That takes sand.

19:57.597 --> 20:01.000
Well, Cellphone Guy,
saddle up next to Sloppy Poppy.

20:01.033 --> 20:03.503
Will: It's not the worst
nickname I've ever had.

20:03.536 --> 20:04.937
I used to be
the Fur Coat Kid,

20:04.971 --> 20:06.873
'cause I had this parka
with, like, a fur hoo--

20:06.906 --> 20:08.040
Oh,
and Turkey Hands Will,

20:08.074 --> 20:09.376
just 'cause my hands
always smelled like turkey.

20:09.409 --> 20:12.445
And Snack Boy. My mom
always packed so many snacks.

20:12.479 --> 20:15.014
Mine was "Elvis,"
'cause of my haircut...

20:15.047 --> 20:17.183
and all my sequined
jump suits.

20:17.216 --> 20:19.018
I was in a real weird phase
for a while.

20:19.051 --> 20:20.353
Wow.

20:20.387 --> 20:21.954
Douglas: Everyone always
called me Donna

20:21.988 --> 20:24.457
because I looked exactly like
my sister, Donna.

20:24.491 --> 20:25.558
May she rest in peace.

20:25.592 --> 20:27.193
Well, look at you now.

20:27.226 --> 20:28.895
Still the losers.

20:28.928 --> 20:31.364
Maybe. But I'm proud to be
a part of this group.

20:31.398 --> 20:32.965
And now, if you would,
drum roll.

20:32.999 --> 20:34.301
Hey.

20:34.334 --> 20:36.669
How many signatures
did we collect?

20:38.938 --> 20:39.972
"Herbie Hind."
[her behind]

20:40.006 --> 20:40.640
[ Laughter ]

20:40.673 --> 20:41.741
Very funny.

20:41.774 --> 20:42.909
Ha!

20:42.942 --> 20:44.611
Herbie Hind.
So clever.

20:44.644 --> 20:47.480
Miggy. Thank you,
but you don't technically count.

20:47.514 --> 20:49.115
"I Saw Your Weiner."
That's not even a name.

20:49.148 --> 20:49.949
I did that!

20:49.982 --> 20:51.784
Thank you.

20:51.818 --> 20:53.453
No cellphones
till eighth grade!

20:53.486 --> 20:55.154
Also, we're never doing
the social night again.

20:55.187 --> 20:56.122
-Absolutely not.
-This was truly awful.

20:56.155 --> 20:57.123
-Never again.
-Horrible!

20:57.156 --> 20:58.124
I love you guys.

20:58.157 --> 20:59.326
[ Sighing ] Oh, gosh.

20:59.359 --> 21:00.960
And you ruined it.
What?

21:00.993 --> 21:02.962
How did I ruin it? I just was
expressing my affection.

21:02.995 --> 21:04.397
I love you, Will.

21:04.431 --> 21:05.665
Thank you, Miggy.
I love you as well.

21:05.698 --> 21:07.867
Everybody get out
of my house.
